1
00:00:04,755 --> 00:00:07,321
[♪♪♪]

2
00:01:05,498 --> 00:01:06,764
My name is Orion.

3
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:11,831
<i>I fled from the fire-pits of Apokolips to warn you.</i>

4
00:01:11,855 --> 00:01:12,965
<i>He's coming.</i>

5
00:01:12,989 --> 00:01:15,073
SUPERMAN: <i>Who is? Darkseid.</i>

6
00:01:16,492 --> 00:01:18,271
<i>He's already provided human agents</i>

7
00:01:18,295 --> 00:01:20,073
<i>with Apokoliptic weaponry.</i>

8
00:01:20,097 --> 00:01:21,563
Maggie!

9
00:01:27,521 --> 00:01:30,338
We're ready to begin phase two, Mr. Mannheim.

10
00:01:37,614 --> 00:01:41,449
You may use this to contact me when you need further help.

11
00:01:53,914 --> 00:01:56,325
Orion was right.

12
00:01:56,349 --> 00:01:57,515
It isn't over.

13
00:02:01,455 --> 00:02:04,216
HAMILTON: We've been monitoring the hot zone by satellite.

14
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:06,119
The explosion triggered a meltdown

15
00:02:06,143 --> 00:02:08,426
in the power plant's central reactor.

16
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:13,526
It's burning straight through the substrata now.

17
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:15,161
And it will get hotter and hotter

18
00:02:15,185 --> 00:02:17,613
until it reaches the Earth's core.

19
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:18,686
What then?

20
00:02:22,692 --> 00:02:26,005
As this simulation shows, it will explode,

21
00:02:26,029 --> 00:02:28,474
setting off a series of violent eruptions

22
00:02:28,498 --> 00:02:31,210
which will cover the earth with more burn holes.

23
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:32,979
I've never seen anything like it.

24
00:02:33,003 --> 00:02:34,814
Yes, you have.

25
00:02:34,838 --> 00:02:36,971
We all have.

26
00:02:38,091 --> 00:02:39,607
On Apokolips.

27
00:03:00,096 --> 00:03:02,508
Your plan worked, Darkseid.

28
00:03:02,532 --> 00:03:04,865
Earth is ours.

29
00:03:06,286 --> 00:03:10,082
Your enthusiasm is premature, Kalibak.

30
00:03:10,106 --> 00:03:14,153
Superman will still try to resist me.

31
00:03:14,177 --> 00:03:15,760
Then send me.

32
00:03:17,898 --> 00:03:18,858
I'm ready.

33
00:03:18,882 --> 00:03:21,599
I'll crush him this time.

34
00:03:24,471 --> 00:03:28,434
Don't remind me of your ignominious defeat.

35
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:31,470
You'll stay at my side where I can see you.

36
00:03:31,494 --> 00:03:33,273
Father, please.

37
00:03:33,297 --> 00:03:38,783
No! This prey requires a more experienced hunter.

38
00:03:47,277 --> 00:03:48,593
Steppenwolf.

39
00:03:49,929 --> 00:03:53,915
I look forward to adding a new trophy to my collection.

40
00:04:04,711 --> 00:04:07,857
The radioactive hole is now only a few hundred meters deep.

41
00:04:07,881 --> 00:04:10,109
But that's going to increase, and quickly.

42
00:04:10,133 --> 00:04:11,611
TURPIN: Shouldn't you be paging

43
00:04:11,635 --> 00:04:13,279
your new best friend the buckethead?

44
00:04:13,303 --> 00:04:15,819
I was just thinking about Orion.

45
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:23,595
What's the matter?

46
00:04:29,719 --> 00:04:31,263
Fried.

47
00:04:31,287 --> 00:04:33,571
Must have been the pulse from the explosion.

48
00:04:36,042 --> 00:04:37,875
We're on our own now.

49
00:04:38,995 --> 00:04:40,873
If the reactor melts through the top mantle,

50
00:04:40,897 --> 00:04:41,913
we'll never stop it.

51
00:04:44,251 --> 00:04:45,783
[♪♪♪]

52
00:04:51,774 --> 00:04:53,474
[ENERGY CRACKLES]

53
00:05:02,002 --> 00:05:04,302
This will be good hunting.

54
00:05:14,764 --> 00:05:16,976
You picked the wrong time, pal.

55
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,349
Ah!

56
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:21,780
[CREATURES SNARLING]

57
00:05:21,804 --> 00:05:23,854
Para-Demons, attack!

58
00:05:30,714 --> 00:05:31,714
Argh!

59
00:05:46,863 --> 00:05:48,379
[HORNS HONKING]

60
00:05:49,615 --> 00:05:52,178
Jeez. We've got a meltdown on Ayers Island,

61
00:05:52,202 --> 00:05:54,062
a war at Sinnott Air Force Base.

62
00:05:54,086 --> 00:05:55,420
What next? [GASPS]

63
00:05:59,242 --> 00:06:00,925
Ah!

64
00:06:01,511 --> 00:06:02,610
[SCREECHES]

65
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:05,663
Whoa.

66
00:06:08,718 --> 00:06:10,802
This wasn't in the forecast.

67
00:06:32,792 --> 00:06:34,192
[SCREAMS]

68
00:06:51,227 --> 00:06:53,077
GIRL: Look at that, Mommy. BOY: I know.

69
00:06:53,863 --> 00:06:55,229
[GRUNTING]

70
00:06:57,233 --> 00:06:58,210
GIRL: Superman.

71
00:06:58,234 --> 00:06:59,234
[GROANS]

72
00:07:01,938 --> 00:07:03,454
Superman!

73
00:07:15,502 --> 00:07:17,935
Now, to the kill.

74
00:07:20,207 --> 00:07:21,472
[CROWD SCREAMING]

75
00:07:25,295 --> 00:07:26,678
WOMAN: Oh, my God!

76
00:07:39,525 --> 00:07:40,541
No!

77
00:08:13,225 --> 00:08:14,390
[GASPS]

78
00:08:18,580 --> 00:08:19,557
Stop him!

79
00:08:19,581 --> 00:08:20,713
[EXPLOSION]

80
00:08:25,553 --> 00:08:28,115
Pull around for another shot.

81
00:08:28,139 --> 00:08:30,139
This guy's about to be an oil slick.

82
00:08:50,562 --> 00:08:52,673
Looks like the big guy could use a hand.

83
00:08:52,697 --> 00:08:53,697
Giacoia, move in!

84
00:08:54,849 --> 00:08:56,182
Come on.

85
00:09:07,228 --> 00:09:08,556
Thanks, inspector.

86
00:09:08,580 --> 00:09:10,530
Hey, don't you have a fire to put out?

87
00:09:14,035 --> 00:09:16,502
[♪♪♪]

88
00:10:52,133 --> 00:10:54,117
[PANTING]

89
00:10:56,988 --> 00:11:01,201
You're a magnificent opponent, Superman.

90
00:11:01,225 --> 00:11:03,788
But even you must realize it's hopeless.

91
00:11:03,812 --> 00:11:05,611
Darkseid.

92
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:11,779
I could easily destroy you now.

93
00:11:11,803 --> 00:11:13,648
And once you're gone,

94
00:11:13,672 --> 00:11:15,282
the pathetic beings of this planet

95
00:11:15,306 --> 00:11:17,651
won't have the will to resist me.

96
00:11:17,675 --> 00:11:20,409
The few who survive, that is.

97
00:11:22,097 --> 00:11:23,097
[GROANING]

98
00:11:24,249 --> 00:11:27,778
However, if you join me as my loyal vassal,

99
00:11:27,802 --> 00:11:31,203
I could guarantee a modicum of restraint.

100
00:11:32,591 --> 00:11:34,869
Think of it, Superman.

101
00:11:34,893 --> 00:11:36,303
The power you have now,

102
00:11:36,327 --> 00:11:38,906
it's nothing compared with what I'm offering you.

103
00:11:38,930 --> 00:11:41,325
You know I can't do that.

104
00:11:41,349 --> 00:11:43,260
Pity.

105
00:11:43,284 --> 00:11:45,896
Still, if you won't be my knight,

106
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,932
you will be my pawn.

107
00:11:47,956 --> 00:11:49,667
[SUPERMAN SCREAMS]

108
00:11:49,691 --> 00:11:52,837
MAN: <i>Citizens are warned to stay away from Metropolis Plaza,</i>

109
00:11:52,861 --> 00:11:55,423
<i>where police are still trying to contain the situation...</i>

110
00:11:55,447 --> 00:11:56,891
Gotta get down there.

111
00:11:56,915 --> 00:11:58,992
Whoa, cowgirl, what are you gonna do?

112
00:11:59,016 --> 00:12:01,896
Hold a gun in one hand and your IV in the other?

113
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:05,433
<i>Forces have been mobilized and are en route to Metropolis.</i>

114
00:12:05,457 --> 00:12:07,240
Dan.

115
00:12:16,751 --> 00:12:19,330
Where's those choppers? I need cover. Now!

116
00:12:19,354 --> 00:12:21,988
[♪♪♪]

117
00:12:36,037 --> 00:12:37,903
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

118
00:12:51,219 --> 00:12:52,946
Outstanding.

119
00:12:52,970 --> 00:12:53,981
[GASPS]

120
00:12:54,005 --> 00:12:56,067
[HISSES]

121
00:12:56,091 --> 00:12:57,457
[SNARLS]

122
00:12:59,845 --> 00:13:01,794
[WHIMPERING]

123
00:13:05,517 --> 00:13:06,494
Thanks, inspector.

124
00:13:06,518 --> 00:13:07,518
Get back!

125
00:13:10,822 --> 00:13:12,450
What do you think you're doin', kid?

126
00:13:12,474 --> 00:13:13,867
This ain't no stunt show.

127
00:13:13,891 --> 00:13:15,837
I'm with the<i> Planet.</i> I'm their photographer.

128
00:13:15,861 --> 00:13:18,477
That a fact? Well, get ready to shoot.

129
00:13:21,799 --> 00:13:24,011
Hey, you overgrown parakeets!

130
00:13:24,035 --> 00:13:25,785
Take a snort of this!

131
00:13:35,330 --> 00:13:37,479
Royer, Colletta, cover me!

132
00:13:45,506 --> 00:13:46,667
That's right, chief.

133
00:13:46,691 --> 00:13:49,020
Turpin and his boys are holding their own.

134
00:13:49,044 --> 00:13:50,404
Maybe even more than that.

135
00:13:50,428 --> 00:13:51,422
[BEEPS]

136
00:13:51,446 --> 00:13:52,840
[CARS HONKING]

137
00:13:52,864 --> 00:13:55,509
[RUMBLING]

138
00:13:55,533 --> 00:13:56,511
What is it?

139
00:13:56,535 --> 00:13:58,929
It ain't no street sweeper.

140
00:13:58,953 --> 00:14:00,886
[CROWD SCREAMING]

141
00:14:19,874 --> 00:14:21,585
What is that thing?

142
00:14:21,609 --> 00:14:23,609
Oh, my Lord.

143
00:14:26,064 --> 00:14:27,630
[WHIMPERS]

144
00:14:30,135 --> 00:14:32,084
[♪♪♪]

145
00:14:34,255 --> 00:14:35,716
Holy Joe.

146
00:14:35,740 --> 00:14:37,807
[GROANING]

147
00:14:58,978 --> 00:15:01,040
Okay, back off. I get the point.

148
00:15:01,064 --> 00:15:03,226
People of Earth,

149
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:06,851
I am Darkseid, lord of Apokolips.

150
00:15:08,055 --> 00:15:12,051
Here is your savior, cowed and broken.

151
00:15:12,075 --> 00:15:15,655
I have crushed him as easily as I have crushed

152
00:15:15,679 --> 00:15:20,410
<i>all who have dared to oppose me throughout the cosmos.</i>

153
00:15:20,434 --> 00:15:23,846
<i>I am power unlike any you have known:</i>

154
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:28,501
<i>absolute, infinite and unrelenting.</i>

155
00:15:28,525 --> 00:15:30,085
<i>You have no choice</i>

156
00:15:30,109 --> 00:15:34,090
<i>but to prepare for a long, dark future as my subjects</i>

157
00:15:34,114 --> 00:15:36,448
and my slaves.

158
00:15:42,972 --> 00:15:44,767
In a pig's eye!

159
00:15:44,791 --> 00:15:47,270
[CROWD SHOUTING]

160
00:15:47,294 --> 00:15:49,005
This is our world, ugly.

161
00:15:49,029 --> 00:15:50,523
You won't get it without a fight!

162
00:15:50,547 --> 00:15:52,775
You hear that, Darkseid?

163
00:15:52,799 --> 00:15:55,778
The people of Earth aren't like your slaves on Apokolips.

164
00:15:55,802 --> 00:15:58,197
They don't take kindly to dictators.

165
00:15:58,221 --> 00:16:01,934
If they resist, I will not hesitate to destroy them.

166
00:16:01,958 --> 00:16:04,804
You want a piece of me? Come on! Come on, rockhead!

167
00:16:04,828 --> 00:16:06,260
[CROWD CHEERING]

168
00:16:10,734 --> 00:16:12,762
Jeez. Is he crazy?

169
00:16:12,786 --> 00:16:13,786
Yeah.

170
00:16:16,156 --> 00:16:18,801
Don't they know this is suicide?

171
00:16:18,825 --> 00:16:22,722
Better a quick death in battle than a slow one under your heel.

172
00:16:22,746 --> 00:16:26,092
Darkseid, we've detected military aircraft

173
00:16:26,116 --> 00:16:27,214
heading this way.

174
00:16:28,718 --> 00:16:31,047
I don't care how many crummy planets you've conquered.

175
00:16:31,071 --> 00:16:32,904
You ain't gettin' this one.

176
00:16:37,977 --> 00:16:39,027
No!

177
00:16:52,159 --> 00:16:54,058
[CROWD CHEERING]

178
00:16:55,128 --> 00:16:56,577
That's one for the home team.

179
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:02,261
Let's finish it.

180
00:17:02,285 --> 00:17:03,513
Very well.

181
00:17:03,537 --> 00:17:05,920
This world dies now.

182
00:17:29,229 --> 00:17:30,873
Darkseid.

183
00:17:30,897 --> 00:17:33,992
High Father has decreed this planet is under his protection.

184
00:17:34,016 --> 00:17:37,463
Any further aggression will breach the peace treaty

185
00:17:37,487 --> 00:17:41,773
and be considered an act of war against New Genesis itself.

186
00:17:45,545 --> 00:17:47,261
The decision is yours, Darkseid.

187
00:17:50,166 --> 00:17:54,564
It is good to see you after all these years, my son.

188
00:17:54,588 --> 00:17:58,834
I've observed your boldness and ferocity for some time

189
00:17:58,858 --> 00:18:02,088
not without undue pride.

190
00:18:02,112 --> 00:18:04,690
Though you're misguided in your loyalty,

191
00:18:04,714 --> 00:18:06,108
I won't quibble

192
00:18:06,132 --> 00:18:09,011
over this insignificant speck in the universe.

193
00:18:09,035 --> 00:18:13,437
I would hate to spoil our reunion with bloodshed.

194
00:18:15,208 --> 00:18:16,674
Return.

195
00:18:21,948 --> 00:18:24,177
Go on, you mangy buzzards.

196
00:18:24,201 --> 00:18:26,262
And don't come back.

197
00:18:26,286 --> 00:18:29,899
Savor your moment of triumph, Superman.

198
00:18:29,923 --> 00:18:33,057
But remember, victory has its price.

199
00:18:35,128 --> 00:18:36,128
[SCREAMS]

200
00:18:38,548 --> 00:18:39,692
Dan!

201
00:18:39,716 --> 00:18:40,926
[CROWD GASPS]

202
00:18:40,950 --> 00:18:42,016
[GASPS]

203
00:18:47,591 --> 00:18:48,606
Murderer!

204
00:18:54,163 --> 00:18:55,341
[GROWLING]

205
00:18:55,365 --> 00:18:56,380
[SCREAMS]

206
00:18:58,734 --> 00:19:01,702
[YELLING]

207
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,890
[BLOWS THUDDING]

208
00:19:17,921 --> 00:19:20,221
[SIGHS]

209
00:19:26,095 --> 00:19:27,394
I'm sorry.

210
00:19:38,024 --> 00:19:41,943
[SINGING IN HEBREW]

211
00:19:58,745 --> 00:20:02,046
<i>♪ Amen ♪</i>

212
00:20:10,473 --> 00:20:13,452
Goodbye, old friend.

213
00:20:13,476 --> 00:20:18,124
In the end, the world didn't really need a super man,

214
00:20:18,148 --> 00:20:21,093
just a brave one.

215
00:20:21,117 --> 00:20:23,667
[♪♪♪]

216
00:20:46,225 --> 00:20:49,577
[♪♪♪]

